parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door latch sensor can cause the door ajar warning light to stay on, leading to battery drain, alarm system malfunction, and inability to lock the doors, which can compromise vehicle safety and security.
symptoms: The door ajar warning light stays on even when the doors are closed
the alarm system sounds randomly
the interior lights remain on
the battery drains frequently
and the doors cannot be locked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including interior lights staying on, alarm system malfunction, and battery drain, which can compromise vehicle safety and security.
symptoms: The interior lights remain on
the alarm system sounds randomly
the battery drains frequently
and various warning lights illuminate on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause brake pedal fade, pedal stiffness, and brake lockup, which can lead to accidents and compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
and the brake pads and rotors are damaged prematurely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, which can lead to engine damage and compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: The engine temperature gauge rises
the cooling fans do not turn on
and the engine overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to extended braking distances and increased stopping times, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels firm or hard
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal has a delayed response
the brake pedal has a hissing sound

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.

the vehicle takes longer to stop

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning shift-to-park warning indicator can cause the vehicle's electrical system to drain, leading to a dead battery and leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The shift-to-park warning indicator illuminates even when the vehicle is in park
causing the entire dashboard to light up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or loss of power can cause the vehicle to become stuck in traffic, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power without warning
